  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Potable water for 400 in rural Mexico</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Independence Aquifer in central Mexico is in a permanent state of decline and contaminated with toxic levels of arsenic and fluoride, which has led to irreversible health complications like dental &amp; crippling skeletal fluorosis in local communities.  This project will provide the training, materials and construction of 29 rainwater-harvesting cisterns and 44 water filter systems for 4 schools, 20 families, and 1 training institute - providing sustainable, safe drinking water for 400+ people.</narrative>
  </description>
